div1.p: Territory of Washington, County of Spokane}ss

Territory of Washington, Plaintiff vs. Ray Raymond Defendant}ss In the District Court of the Territory of Washington, and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney Spokane Falls, Spokane County, in said Territory.
To the Sheriff of Spokane County Greeting: In the Name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon George Wycoff

to be and appear before the District Court at the Court House, in Cheney Spokane Falls in said County, on the forthwith day of December A.D. 1886 at o'clock M. to there give evi dence in the above entitled cause on the part of said Defendant Ray Raymond.
Witness the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed this 7th day of Dec. A.D. 1886.
D.A. Clement Clerk
By Deputy.
Territory of Washington, County of Spokane}ss
I hereby certify that I served the within Subpoena on the within named witness by reading the same to him in said County, on this 11th day of December A.D. 1886.
E.F. Whittier Sheriff
By Deputy.
Case No.
SUBPOENA
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington, and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney Spokane Falls Spokane County, in said Territory.
Territory Plaintiff
vs.
Ray Raymond Defendant
Returned and filed this 11th day of Dec. A.D. 1886 D.A. Clement Clerk By Deputy
SHERIFF'S FEES Serving 1 names .40 .40 Mileage 128 miles at .10 12.80 Total, - - - - $13.20

Territory of Washington County of Spokane}ss I hereby certify that I have this 8th day of December 1886 appointed W.B. Banhorn as a Special Deputy Sheriff to serve the within subpoena on the within named witness George Wycoff.
Dated this 8th day of Dec. 1886
E.F. Whittier Sheriff of Spokane County W.T.
